        <num>CCP 2</num>
        <heading>2.  Jurisdiction over subject matter</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2.  Jurisdiction over subject matter
Jurisdiction over the subject matter is the legal power and authority of a court to hear and determine a particular class of actions or proceedings, based upon the object of the demand, the amount in dispute, or the value of the right asserted.</p>
        </content>
